<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-25T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="60" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/67<hi rend="superscript">7/24</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-25T11:00:00-04:00">May 25, 1940—11 a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>103. Your telegram No. 84, May 23, noon.<note n="69" xml:id="d60fn1">See footnote 29, <ref target="#pg_16">p.
                                            16</ref>.</note> Saw the Minister for Foreign
                                        Affairs<note n="70" xml:id="d60fn2">Abraham Ortega.</note>
                                    at 7:30 last night. He said he had been favoring something of
                                    the sort and would see the President<note n="71" xml:id="d60fn3">Pedro Aguirre Cerda.</note> today and try to give a
                                    definite answer by night. I saw the President at dinner last
                                    night and prepared him for today’s conference with the Minister.
                                    Confident of acceptance.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>